# Line-ending normalization.
#
# Keep tracked TOML at LF on every OS. A Windows checkout — or a Pkg operation
# that rewrites a TOML in place (e.g. `Pkg.instantiate` re-sorting
# julia/kernel/Project.toml on Windows) — would otherwise introduce CRLF churn
# into tracked config and pollute cross-OS diffs. `eol=lf` makes git store and
# check out LF regardless of platform.
#
# NOTE for reviewers: a Pkg op also REORDERS [deps]/[sources] and STRIPS TOML
# comments (it cannot preserve them). Do NOT commit a Pkg-rewritten Project.toml
# that drops the [sources]/[compat] rationale comments or reorders entries —
# revert it with `git checkout -- <file>` and keep the hand-authored version.
*.toml text eol=lf
